abstract: THIS year's Young Americans Craft Competition, the nation  wide contest sponsored by the American Craft Council, was devoted to metal craftsmen, and an exhibition of the winners' work opens tomorrow at the Museum of Contemporary Crafts, 44 West 53d Street.

abstract: Dr. and Mrs. John Collins Harvey of Bethesda, Md., have announced the engagement of their daughter, Amy Lavinia Ryan Harvey, to Ens. Loren Fitzhugh Reese, U.S.N., son of Mr. and Mrs. Robert Bacon Reese of Washington. A July wedding is planned.

abstract: The engagement of Priscilla Adams Fenton to Ralph Lowell 3d, son of Mr. and Mrs. Lowell Jr. of Westwood, Mass., has been announced by Mr. and Mrs. Paul F. Fenton Jr. of Hanover, N.H., and Dark Harbor, Me., parents of the future bride.

WHEN the members of the New York State Senate assemble tomorrow for the day's proceedings, the in  vocation opening the session will be delivered by a woman for the first time in the history of the state.

Dr. and Mrs. Earle W. Brauer of New York and Westport, Conn., have announced the engagement of their daughter, Amy Brauer, to Coleman W. Hoyt Jr. of Concord, Mass. He is a son of Mr. Hoyt of Waccabuc, N.Y., and Woodstock, Vt., and Mrs. Louis V. Farrar of Katonah, N.Y.
headline_main: Amy Brauer, Engaged to Coleman Hoyt Jr.
